Global.instructorsImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing instructor (code), the instructor data will be updated unless the code is for student or employee.
If the instructor’s department is not in the instructor’s faculty departments, this instructor will be ignored.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every instructor: (code, name, nationality, faculty, department)
Global.hallsImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing hall or building (code), the hall data will be updated.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every hall: (building name, location name, faculty)
Global.employeesImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing employee (code), the employee data will be updated unless the code is for instructor or student.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every employee: (code, name)
Global.departmentsImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing department (code), the department data will be updated.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every department: (code, name, faculty).
Global.coursesImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing course (code), the course data will be updated.
If the course's program or bylaw is not in the course's faculty, this course will be ignored.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every course: (code, name, faculty, department, bylaw).
Global.studentsImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing student (code), the student data will be updated unless the code is for instructor or employee.
If the student's program is not in the student's faculty, this student will be ignored.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every student: (code, name, nationality, faculty, bylaw, program, first semester).
Global.offeringsImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing offering, the offering data including registrations and marks will be updated.
If the course does not exist in a Bylaw in the offering faculty, the offering will be ignored.
If the student’s faculty does not match the course’s faculty, this student registration will be ignored. 
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every offering: (First Sheet: term name, course code, faculty) (Second Sheet: student code, grades)
Global.transactionsImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing transaction which has been imported before using this file, the transaction data be updated.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every transaction: (Invoice ID, Student Code, Transaction Amount, Payment Date)
Global.invoicesImportMessage:
Please make sure that all cells in the first row of the exported file remain the same in the file you are trying to import.
If you are importing an existing invoice which has been imported before using this file, the invoice data will be updated.
The following fields are mandatory to be filled in the imported file for every transaction: (student code, service type, academic year, invoice amount, invoice currency)
